rComments: It was his first time teaching online, and his teaching format was to post powerpoints and optional readings. The powerpoints weren't too long, so it was pretty easy to go through the material. 2 cumulative midterms and an exam. Overall I learnt the relevant basics of genomics - sequencing methods, alignments, analysis, etc. Great prof and course!

This class was one of the hardest classes I've ever taken. However the course material is very interesting and useful if you plan to do graduate studies. This prof's exam are not easy, not enough practice questions or assignments to prepare the students for the exam. You cannot ask him questions by e-mail. You have to go to his office.

He comes across as helpful, but would rather the course being done fast than more appropriately preparing students for his exams. The exams, by the way, are 100% thinking outside the box-type questions, and are worth a lot. Finally, his availability is really bad (must make an appointment to see him in his office, doesnt respond to emails).

Really nice and helpful prof, clear explanations. The course had one midterm worth 50% and one presentation worth 50%. The midterm did ask some questions about protistology history (who came up with different terms, for example). Course ended three weeks before the end of the semester, which was awesome.

Overall it was a good class. I found the midterm quit difficult and did not reflect what was covered in class.  Prof. Corradi is a good teacher and is quit helpful with his feedback for the research proposal and presentation.
